Entry.JapaneseText: ベッドを 貸してください！
Entry.EnglishText: We need a bed right now!

Entry.JapaneseText: レスター博士の 知り合い……？
Entry.EnglishText: Is this one of your acquaintances?

Entry.JapaneseText: ああ、彼女は うちの助手のミラルドだ
とにかく早く、 彼女をベッドに！
Entry.EnglishText: At any rate, let's put her in a bed quickly!

Entry.JapaneseText: <Red>熱砂の洞窟<White>で お会いしたんです
Entry.EnglishText: We found her at the Cavern of Burning Sand.

Entry.JapaneseText: たぶん、魔物に やられたんだと思うぜ
Entry.EnglishText: I can't believe she handled all the monsters to the way there, though.

Entry.JapaneseText: 君たち、 本当に<Red>熱砂の洞窟<White>に……
Entry.EnglishText: You guys...really went to the Cavern of Burning Sand...

Entry.JapaneseText: だが、 ミラルドがどうして？
Entry.EnglishText: But what was Milard doing there...

Entry.JapaneseText: さあ……精霊と契約しようと してたみたいだけど
Entry.EnglishText: She looked like she wanted to form a pact with the Summon Spirit...

Entry.JapaneseText: もしかして、ミラルドさん、 <KLA>さんにもう一度、 研究をがんばってもらいたくて……
Entry.EnglishText: Could it be... that Miss Milard wanted to cheer up <KLA> so he took up his investigation again?

Entry.JapaneseText: 彼女の才なら アルヴァニスタの 高等研究員になれる
Entry.EnglishText: She was an old colleague of mine from the Alvanista Research Academy.

Entry.JapaneseText: 彼女は私のような異端分子の ところで、その生涯を 履き潰すべきではないんだ
Entry.EnglishText: She participated in the sin I committed and her career was crushed.

Entry.JapaneseText: すっかり私に愛想を尽かして 研究所にでも行ってしまったと 思っていたのに……
Entry.EnglishText: She always was looking after me and complementing me for my research, even though I couldn't get my mind out of it...

Entry.JapaneseText: 何を吹き込まれたか 知らないけど……
Entry.EnglishText: But regardless, I knew I had to inspire you...

Entry.JapaneseText: アルヴァニスタの研究員に なるのが私の幸せだなんて、 あなたは本気で思っているの？
Entry.EnglishText: I was happy doing all that research along with you in Alvanista...Have you really ever thought otherwise?

Entry.JapaneseText: どうして……私の気持ちを 聞いてくれないの？
Entry.EnglishText: Why have you never listened to my feelings?

Entry.JapaneseText: ……私は父と同じ過ちを おかしたくなかっただけだ
Entry.EnglishText: ...I didn't want to repeat the same mistakes of my father.

Entry.JapaneseText: 草花を探して家に帰らず、 帰ってくれば、研究室に何日も 閉じこもりきり
Entry.EnglishText: He'd leave the house for days, looking for things he never disclosed to us. When he finally returned home he would shut himself in his room for god knows how many days.

Entry.JapaneseText: 研究に没頭し、家族を顧みない父を 私は憎んでさえいたのかもしれない
Entry.EnglishText: The more he worked on his research, the less he came home. You have no idea how much I hated him.

Entry.JapaneseText: 何よりも母は幸せだっただろうか？ ずっとそれが頭から離れなかった
Entry.EnglishText: Do you think my mother was happy at all? She got beaten up ever since I have memory...

Entry.JapaneseText: ……私もおまえに母と同じことを 強いているのではと思った
Entry.EnglishText: I didn't want you to go through what my mother has ...

Entry.JapaneseText: 私があなたのために ここにいるなんて、 自惚れないで
Entry.EnglishText: I'm here just for you...Don't worry about things like that...

Entry.JapaneseText: <KLA>。 私は好きでここにいるのよ
Entry.EnglishText: <KLA>. I like to be here with you.

Entry.JapaneseText: もしかしたら、私にも、 別の形の幸せもあるでしょう
Entry.EnglishText: It could be at times I might not particularly show that I'm happy.

Entry.JapaneseText: でも、今が幸せなのに、 他のものを求める必要がある？
Entry.EnglishText: But right now I'm brimming with happiness... Do I really need anything else?

Entry.JapaneseText: きっと……あなたのお母様も 私と同じ気持ちだったと、思う
Entry.EnglishText: I know without a doubt... I know what you felt for your mom, I truly do.

Entry.JapaneseText: いや、ありがとう。 ミラルド
あ、す、すまない…… 君たちも。悪かった
Entry.EnglishText: I-I'm sorry... All right, got it.

Entry.JapaneseText: それで？ 精霊の力を 集めるために私に力を 借してほしいというのは……
Entry.EnglishText: What's next? You wanted the Summon Spirit's and my own strength to...

Entry.JapaneseText: 魔術の暴走を止めるのよね
Entry.EnglishText: To stop magic from going rampant.

Entry.JapaneseText: はい。その、 『虹輪』を消すために
Entry.EnglishText: That's right, it is to erase the "Prism Ring."

Entry.JapaneseText: その契約の指輪っての 貸してくれよ
Entry.EnglishText: That's why we'll take the Pact Ring for a while.

Entry.JapaneseText: ……すまないが、契約の指輪は とても貴重なものでね、簡単に 貸せるものではないんだ
Entry.EnglishText: ...I'm sorry but that Pact Ring is way too important, I can't just lend it to you guys that easily.

Entry.JapaneseText: 契約の指輪は、 現代の技術では作れないし、 修理するのも難しい
Entry.EnglishText: The technology that created the rings doesn't exist anymore, if it were to break it'd be extre<MEL>y hard to be repaired.

Entry.JapaneseText: 残っている数も少ない。 それほど貴重なものなんだ。 悪いが……
Entry.EnglishText: It's the last of its kind left. That's why it's so important. I'm sorry.

Entry.JapaneseText: ……しょうがないよ…… あきらめて他の方法を 探すしか……
Entry.EnglishText: ...There's nothing we can do, so we'll have to search for a new way...

Entry.JapaneseText: ただ精霊の力が必要と いうだけなら、他にも 方法はあるかもしれないな
Entry.EnglishText: If you still want to have the Spirit's power there is another way we can go about this.

Entry.JapaneseText: <Red>ヴァルハラ<White>の バジルという学者なら 何か知ってるかもしれない
Entry.EnglishText: You could come into contact with Valhalla's rese<ARC>r, Basil.

Entry.JapaneseText: ああ、私が一緒に行って 話を通してやろう
Entry.EnglishText: I'll go with you to talk with him.

Entry.JapaneseText: イフリートを連れてきたら、 協力するという約束だったしな
Entry.EnglishText: After all you did complete our promise and gain Efreet's power.

Entry.JapaneseText: やった！ サンキュー！ レスター博士！
喜ぶのはバジルに 会ってからだ
Entry.EnglishText: I'd be glad to meet Basil.

Entry.JapaneseText: それから、 私のことは<KLA>でいい
そうね、その博士って なんか気持ち悪いもの
Entry.EnglishText: That's right! Calling him "renowned" truly feels wrong, doesn't it?

Entry.JapaneseText: 気持ち悪いってな…… まぁ、いいか。 それじゃあ……
Entry.EnglishText: What do you "feels wrong"...? Anyways, let's go.

Entry.JapaneseText: ちょっと出かけてくる
Entry.EnglishText: I'll be leaving for a while.
